programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Choices
programme.desc: The parents of two Vietnamese children come to America to look for them after a ten-year separation.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Summer Camp
programme.desc: After having been scarred in a fire, an actress becomes a counselor at a summer camp for blind children. The camp is run by Jonathan and Mark's blind friend Frank.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Inner Limits
programme.desc: A young man decides to institutionalize his brother who has been completely paralyzed and speechless for many years, against the wishes of their mother.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: It's a Dog's Life
programme.desc: Mark believes that God has turned Jonathan into a dog. Meanwhile, he must contend with a runaway kid and the kid's scatterbrained mother.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Merry Christmas from Grandpa
programme.desc: On Christmas Eve, Jonathan shows three men what will happen in the future if the Earth continues to be ravaged by pollution. One of the men is an energy official another is a farmer and the third one is the President.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Pilot - Part 1
programme.desc: In the series opener, we meet Jonathan Smith, a probationary angel who has been sent to help people on Earth. He befriends residents at a retirement home. The administrator at the home has a brother named Mark who is suspicious of Jonathan.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Pilot - Part 2
programme.desc: Jonathan helps the residents of Havencrest, when they learn that the retirement home is going to be sold. Jonathan must reveal his real identity to Mark in order to complete the assignment.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: All The Right Career Moves
programme.desc: Nancy has now recovered from a long illness and is ready to reenter the workforce. Our experts give her the polish and edge she will need to land a new position. Will Nancy go from"left on the shelf" to being a"hot commodity" and look ten years young.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Blackbelt Beauty
programme.desc: Donna is a former Marine, a karate brown belt and a single mom with not much time for herself. Donna enters her journey with her "No Pain, No Gain" Marine attitude, and surrenders to The Glam Squad and their team of experts.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Trials of Tracy
programme.desc: Tracy is a New York City lawyer who can't find a man. Her frumpy wardrobe and thick glasses keep her home buried in her books for fear of rejection. But our team is on the case to bring this lonely lawyer out of her shell and gain some needed confidence.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Jayne Lowe
programme.desc: Woking wife and mother Jayne Lowe is at an all time low. After a high-flying career as an air-hostess, she has come down to earth with a bump, as a stay-at-home mum of three under-five's. Can Nicki Hambleton-Jones make Jayne look ten years younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Reconstructing Bernie
programme.desc: A construction worker by trade, Bernie is a man's man. So while years of backbreaking labor in the sun has taken its toll on his body, Bernie hasn't been taking care of himself. Time to make Bernie look 10 Years Younger!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Donna Fuller
programme.desc: Derby wife and mum Donna Fuller is stuck at home and stuck in a rut. Her biggest problem is her gapped front teeth, which have left her, literally, with nothing to smile about. Can Nicky Hambleton-Jones and the team make Debbie look 10 years younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Bikini Special - Heather Williams
programme.desc: NHS Manager Heather Williams is the perfect candidate: after a weight loss of five stones and three years of four times a week gym workouts, all that remained of her former size 20 body was a sack of excess skin covering a tiny 4 foot eleven frame.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Singing A New Tune
programme.desc: April lost a front tooth in a horseback riding accident and never smiles. Her passion is singing, and she'd like to stand on stage without embarrassment. Will an orthodontic overhaul and a full Glam assault drop years from her appearance?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Independence Day
programme.desc: Recently divorced and about to send her daughter off to college, Candice is embarking on a new phase in life. Alone and worried about feeling old and unattractive, Candice has come for help to boost her spirits.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Debbie Ashcroft "One Year On"
programme.desc: 46 year old Debbie Ashcroft was a lifelong smoker and sunbed addict with the peculiar habit of bleaching her hair up to six times a week. A year later Nicky visits Debbie to find out if she's permanently kicked all the bad habits.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Sewing The Seeds To A New Look
programme.desc: Melissa has the perfect Beverly Hills fashion career, working with the finest made-to-order clothing. But when the exclusive clientele see her missing teeth, the impression is not what she would like. She also desperately wants to update her look.
programme.sub-title: Sewing The Seeds To A New Look

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: 80 lbs. Down, 10 Years To Go
programme.desc: After struggling with health issues Cheryl has recently lost 80 pounds and needs her appearance to catch up to her body. She is single and ready to start dating again. Cheryl's new makeover will help her hit the dating scene with a renewed attitude.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Grey Skies To Blue
programme.desc: Between her busy family life, and a scrapbook business on the side, Christine barely has time for herself. After 20 years of marriage and three kids, she's in need of a makeover and some serious rekindled romance.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: A Prescription For Youth
programme.desc: New Mom Amber has her work cut out for her. In her early teens she was diagnosed with Crohn's disease, which resulted in unwanted physical side effects. Watch the team of experts make Amber look 10 Years Younger.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 9
programme.desc: The family are making arrangements to leave Leopard's Den, all except Du Plessis who is steadfastly refusing to accept that he has lost his home. He won't use his share of the money from the sale of the land to buy somewhere else.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 10
programme.desc: The family have been squatting at Leopard's Den as they prepare to make their last stand to prevent the bulldozers from destroying their home. Du Plessis and Fatani bring elephants and a giraffe to dissuade the construction crew from moving in.

programme.title: Wild At Heart
programme.desc: After the devastating loss of Leopard's Den, the family are split across continents. Caroline, Liv and a heavily pregnant Alice are in the UK, while Danny and Du Plessis have remained in South Africa.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: Danny and Ed release two cheetah brothers together, a symbol of their new partnership, but not all of the family are happy about this new start. Caroline is still furious at what she sees as Danny's betrayal of Du Plessis.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6
programme.desc: Danny is in prison, accused of murdering Peeters, but Du Plessis is determined to prove his friend's innocence by any means he can. Du Plessis' first attempt backfires disastrously when he harangues a police officer and ends up in a cell next to Danny.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 4
programme.desc: A Glenbrook farmer has been left seriously injured after one of his Highland cows has taken to him with its horns.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 5
programme.desc: The team are being sent out to a traumatic accident that will end up being rather close to home.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 6
programme.desc: The Rescue chopper team is en route to Whitianga to help save a badly injured stock car driver.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 7
programme.desc: The chopper team are about to take off to rescue a seriously injured man.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: 55-year-old Gold Coast holidaymaker Irina is in real trouble - she's caught in a deadly ocean rip. Like many tourists, Irena was unaware of the risks of not swimming between the beach flags. The Gold Coast rescue helicopter spots her in the nick of time.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: A head-on car collision in Tasmania has left tourists Hong and Xeu Wu fighting for their lives. Ambulance crews have managed to stabilize Mr. Wu but Mrs. Wu is in a critical condition and calling out for her husband.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: A team of amateur scuba divers find themselves in deep trouble when their boat capsizes off Sydney's Botany Bay. The Westpac La Perouse crew spots the distressed divers while on a routine training mission.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: 65-year old Dave, a surf skier, is attacked and bitten by a Great White shark while training in the ocean. Dehydrated (after four days at sea), Margo needs urgent hospital care.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: A car crashes another car at a country intersection. It's situation critical with four people trapped. It turns out someone was running from the police – and he was on drugs.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 8
programme.desc: The chopper team is responding to a life threatening emergency.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 9
programme.desc: The team have received a status 2 callout; Mark Lorimer was knocked out and has multiple injuries after being hit head-on by another vehicle.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 10
programme.desc: The team are called to a road accident where a woman has been cut from inside of her wrecked car.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 11
programme.desc: The team is responding to a life-threatening emergency. A cyclist in his 60s, Terrence Williams, is unresponsive and critical after an accident 15 minutes flying time from Auckland, near the small settlement of Maramarua.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 12
programme.desc: The team are called out to a status 2 emergency; Clark Chamberlain was abseiling when he fell from the top of a cliff to the ground. He's now in a critical condition suffering from multiple injuries.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3
programme.desc: Tasmania Police is on high alert after a prisoner escapes from jail. The man is armed and dangerous. The Rescue Helicopter is called in to assist with the manhunt. Things turn deadly when they spot him.

programme.title: Supercars: German Supercars
programme.desc: They are long and heavy, and they are German: the A8 Audi does not do much downsizing as well as the large executive cars from BMW or the luxurious VW Phaeton. The big players of the premium car manufacturers!

programme.title: Supercars: Motor Show Geneva
programme.desc: There are details which set supercars apart from normal cars and these details are essential. Supercars are the biggest, loudest and most expensive cars on the highway; they're four-wheeled works of art.

programme.title: Supercars: V8 Power
programme.desc: The 'facelift' of the new Mercedes E cost around one billion euros! But it is only one part of the exclusivity of the new E 63 AMG. Of course, the high performance brand of Mercedes-Benz added several other features!

programme.title: Supercars: British Power
programme.desc: Very British: power and performance, craftsmanship and design. We have a look at the most beautiful cars of Aston Martin, Bentley and Rolls-Royce.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Fastest Cars in the World
programme.desc: In this episode, we decide what's hot and what's not in the glamorous world of cars. This time we've decided to focus on the fastest cars.
programme.sub-title: The Fastest Cars in the World

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Most Expensive Production Cars
programme.desc: Real luxury. The kind of cars that you only dream of. On today's Top Ten Show, we're going to expose the most expensive cars in production.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Ten Slowest Cars
programme.desc: Usually, when you talk about cars, it's all about their speed and velocity. But this time we’ve decided to turn the tables and are going to show you the opposite end of the spectrum: the ten most sluggish cars.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Ten Most Fuel-efficient Cars
programme.desc: Fuel prices keep going up. Oil companies are justifying this with high demands and rising oil prices. And the prices will carry-on going up. So on today's show we are showing you ten of the most fuel-efficient cars.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Most Unusual Cars of Modern Times
programme.desc: Day in day out, R&D departments of car manufacturers ponder over about what constitutes the perfect car. It has to be extraordinary. It has to stand out and it has to be unique.
programme.sub-title: The Most Unusual Cars of Modern Times

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Most Successful Cars in the 24h Race
programme.desc: The 24-hour-race at the German Nürburgring is one of the most famous and dangerous long-distance races in the world and in today's program we'll show you the cars that have won the most titles each year.
programme.sub-title: The Most Successful Cars in the 24h Race

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Most Affordable Hybrid Models
programme.desc: In today's show, we are going to show you the most affordable hybrid models. The trail-blazers are definitely the Japanese, who have a whole bunch of cars to offer.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Oldest Car Manufacturers
programme.desc: It’s time to get nostalgic: who do you think is the most important pioneer of the automotive world? We do a little time travel and trace back the trail of the modern car.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Greatest Car Legends
programme.desc: Some cars are not just a means of transport, but influenced entire generations and became legends on their own. That’s why we won’t talk about expensive, fast or successful cars on this episode.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Ugliest Cars
programme.desc: The car-manufacturers' design departments are constantly tinkering around, in a quest to invent the perfect car. And more often than not, very elegantly-shaped cars are the result.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Most Beautiful Cars
programme.desc: Today we are going for Lux. It has been said that beauty is in the eye of the beholder. So we promise to maintain some objectivity. Desirable cars are what we want, and what we shall get.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Murder in a Bottle

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: John 3:16

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Body in the Freezer
programme.desc: A meeting between two businessmen leaves one shot in the face. Things seem cut and dry until Lt. Kenda realizes the “victim” could actually be the aggressor, shot struggling over his own gun.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Death Rains Down
programme.desc: Restaurant worker Sharon Coleman is murdered in a hail of large caliber gunfire. Kenda must break through a web of lies to hunt down one of the most dangerous criminal masterminds he’s ever faced.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Blood Red Highway
programme.desc: The elderly owners of a local grocery are attacked and left for dead. Working with a vague witness description, Lt. Joe Kenda leads a state-wide manhunt to catch a pair of cold-blooded killers.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Fate Worst Than Death
programme.desc: At the bottom of a steep ravine, joggers discover a body mutilated beyond recognition. To catch a ruthless maniac, Lt. Joe Kenda must first solve the puzzle of the victim’s identity.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: The Master Key
programme.desc: When a pregnant mother and her two young sons are brutally slain, pressure mounts for the CSPD to catch the cold-blooded monster who did it.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Weapon of Choice
programme.desc: When mother of two Shaundra Murr is run over in front of her house, officers initially suspect a hit and run. Until Lt. Joe Kenda uncovers evidence proving Shaundra’s murder was a crime of passion.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Princess Cujo, Prada, and Bearz
programme.desc: Los Angeles Lakers executive Jeanie Buss asks Cesar to take the "Cujo" out of Princess. Prada, a pampered Pomeranian throws vicious temper tantrums, and Bearz, a Rottweiler attacks shopping carts.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Seven, Sara, and Madeliene
programme.desc: Jillian Michael’s Greyhound mix barks and nips at her horse. A German Shorthaired Pointer is an escape artist. A Yorkie demonstrates fear aggression of brooms and car windshield wipers.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: The Dark Side of Chipper
programme.desc: Chipper, a 2-month old Ridgeback/Boxer mix has become progressively more aggressive and has attacked 5 dogs. Two Whippets, Rudy and Monte, are causing issues at their owner’s place of business.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Bull-Whipped
programme.desc: Aggressive bulldog Hugo is sent to canine rehab, and fellow bulldog Crusty must overcome his dominance issues if he's ever going to enjoy walks.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Lives Changed
programme.desc: In this special episode, Cesar revisits some of the incredible Dog Whisperer stories of the past four years and shares his reactions to the changes in the lives of these special packs.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Sadie and Calder
programme.desc: Allen and Erin Carrasco ‘s Basset Hound Sadie whines and moans whenever Allen is around. Blue Heeler mix Calder is a great dog by day, but bedtime rituals unleash unwelcome night terrors.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Mascot Mayhem
programme.desc: A German shepherd might be evicted because of his barking, and a bulldog with behavior issues isn't welcome at her owner's café. Can Cesar help?

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Army Brats
programme.desc: At an army base, Cesar helps an Australian shepherd scared of men in uniform and a Shetland shepherd who barks non-stop when planes fly overhead.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Ketchup_Mustard

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: My Crazy Obsession Christmas Spcl 2

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Identical Twin Obsession / Eats Mattresses
programme.desc: Twins Amy and Becky are addicted to being identical, looking alike, acting alike, and even weighing their meals to stay the same size. Jennifer is addicted to eating mattresses.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Extreme Hair/Addicted to Bee Stings
programme.desc: Asha hasn't cut her 21-foot long hair in nearly a quarter century and spends up to six hours a day grooming her ten-pound locks. Margaret has stung herself over 50,000 times with bees.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: My Crazy Obsession Pilot
programme.desc: My Collection Obsession takes you deep inside the world of four of the country’s most obsessed collectors each taking their material obsession to jaw-dropping extremes.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Sucker/Bodybuilder

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Mouse Mania_Wigged Out

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Eats Bricks / Married To A Carnival Ride

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Addicted to Being Pamela Anderson

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Air Freshener / Long Neck

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Older Women/ Madonna

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Airline Addict_Crazy for Capybaras

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Casting / Psychics

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Bayou Baby
programme.desc: Chris and Jessica are going back to their roots and looking for a bayou home near Houma, Louisiana. But with a rambunctious baby, finding the perfect waterfront home can be a challenge.
